**Summary**: I was unable to find a way to rename an _alias to any tuples or arrays_

**Version Used**: 17.7.0 Preview 1.0 [33603.545.main].

**Steps to Reproduce**:

1. Create an alias to a tuple or array
2. Code to create a type using the alias
3. Ctl R-R to rename and alter it (I changed the case of the first letter in arrayExample or TupleExample)

```
using TupleExample = (string, int);
using arrayExample = int[];
using S1 = string;

namespace ConsoleApp22
{
    internal class Class1
    {
        public void F(TupleExample x)
        {
            S1 s = "";
            TupleExample a = ("sdf", 42);
            arrayExample b = { 3, 4, 5 };
            Console.WriteLine(a.ToString(), b);
        }
    }
}
```

**Diagnostic Id**: CS0246 Type or namespace not found


**Expected Behavior**:

The same as for renaming the string alias in the example. This is partway through changing S1 to s1.

![aliasbug1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5844318/229906610-acbd2f01-d00b-49ef-9764-8cca9699a0fd.png)


As the popup text is changed, and the underlying alias is updated, the code that will be changed is marked in green and no error appears.

**Actual Behavior**:

As the popup text is changed, the underlying alias is updated, but this makes the uses of it invalid and gives the CS0246 error at the use site. 

Also, I did not find a way to exit the dialog without hitting ESC.

![aliasbug2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5844318/229906618-73d55ab6-a82f-499d-8ec5-c3563c7c84bc.png)

**Additional Notes**: 

I also tried by changing the name and hitting Ctl-period. It suggests a rename, however it does nothing.

